y combination of $f(R,X,\\phi)$\ngravities with the above string-corrected Einstein Gauss-Bonnet models can\nyield $c_T^2=1$, with $X=\\frac{1}{2}\\partial_{\\mu}\\phi\\partial^{\\mu}\\phi $.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Aug 2019 18:14:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-02"}
