smaller (resp. larger) than 1, it contains\na finite (resp. infinite) number of algebraic integers totally in it. For\ninstance, for real line segments, the limit length is 4.\n  This paper is written as part of a collective project conducted in \\'Ecole\nPolytechnique (France). It is aimed towards undergraduate audience in\nmathematics, with basic knowledge in algebra, topology, analysis, and dwells\ninto a modern topic of research.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Aug 2019 19:06:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 29 Nov 2019 19:40:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-03"}
